                           <!-- Unable to parse values for the "ana" attribute on the "objectDesc"
                                nor for the "objectType" element to be included in the paragraph
                                below. These will need to be added manually.-->
                           <p>Thick marble slab with handle cut out on the left side.The handle measures 23x6 cm. It is oval at the top but is turned down at the bottom edges, which also show some signs of wear. Tool marks are visible inside the handle. The back of the slab is roughly chiseled for bonding. There are also light traces of gray plaster.</p>
                              <dimensions type="surface" unit="cm">
                                 <width>61.6</width>
                                 <height>36.1</height>
                                 <depth>6.0</depth>
                              </dimensions>
                        </support>
                        <condition ana="#complete.broken">
                           <!--provide appropriate values for the "ana" attribute from the USEP vocabulary-->
                           <p>The top left corner of the tablet (containing D. and the top part of the handle) has broken off the remainder of the tablet. Additionally, the right-hand side of the tablet is not fully intact - while the main text has been preserved, the M. is only partially visible.</p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" writtenLines="8">
                           <p>The majority of the text (7 lines) is located within a thinly incised frame. D. M. is placed outside of this frame. These two letters are positioned in the top right and left hand corners, respectively, and are equidistant from the frame. The top of each letter lies on the same horizontal axis as the top part of the frame. These letters are similar in size with the rest of the text.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
